'''Aulus Egnatius Priscillianus''' (c. 135 - 1??) was a Roman [[philosopher]].

He married and had [[Lucius Egnatius Victor]], [[Quintus Egnatius Proculus (suffect consul 219)|Quintus Egnatius Proculus]] and [[Aulus Egnatius Proculus]] as sons.{{Citation needed|date=January 2010}}

He was also related to [[Marcus Egnatius Marcellinus]] and [[Marcus Egnatius Postumus]].

