{{Infobox Officeholder | name =Pál Szende | image =SzendePal.jpg | order =[[Minister of Finance of Hungary]] | term_start =25 November 1918 | term_end =21 March 1919 | president = | predecessor =[[Mihály Károlyi]] | successor =[[Jenő Varga]] | birth_date ={{Birth date|df=yes|1879|02|07}} | birth_place =[[Nyírbátor]], [[Austria-Hungary]] | death_date={{Death date and age|1934|07|15|1879|02|07|df=y}} | death_place=[[Seini]], [[Kingdom of Romania]] | profession =politician, economist | party =Civil Radical Party |}} {{eastern name order|Szende Pál}} '''Pál Szende''' (born as '''Pál Schwarz''', 7 February 1879 – 15 July 1934) was a [[Hungary|Hungarian]] politician, who served as [[Minister of Finance]] between 1918 and 1919. From 1904 he worked as a lawyer. He participated in the radical political movement along with [[Oszkár Jászi]]. After the establishment of the [[Hungarian Soviet Republic]] he lived in [[Vienna]]. Szende took part in the [[Austrian Civil War]] after that he escaped to [[Czechoslovakia]] then [[Romania]], where he died.
